## ğŸ“Œ Nano Editor Basics (Shortcuts)

When youâ€™re inside `nano`, shortcuts are shown at the bottom.
ğŸ‘‰ The `^` means **Ctrl key**.

| Action            | Shortcut   |
| ----------------- | ---------- |
| Save file         | `Ctrl + O` |
| Exit nano         | `Ctrl + X` |
| Cut line          | `Ctrl + K` |
| Paste line        | `Ctrl + U` |
| Search text       | `Ctrl + W` |
| Go to line number | `Ctrl + _` |
| Justify paragraph | `Ctrl + J` |

Example flow:

1. Open file â†’ `nano notes.txt`
2. Type some text
3. Save â†’ `Ctrl + O`, press Enter
4. Exit â†’ `Ctrl + X`

